<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: theatre stage -->
  <VFEC_TheatreStage.label>剧院舞台</VFEC_TheatreStage.label>
  <!-- EN: A lightly decorated wooden stage meant to provide area for props and actors both to create compelling scenes. Such performances are quite fun for both those on stage and those casting their eyes upon it. -->
  <VFEC_TheatreStage.description>一个有少许装饰的木制舞台，演员们可以在这里上演戏剧。这种活动不管对演员和观众来说都很愉快。</VFEC_TheatreStage.description>
  
  <!-- EN: thermaebath -->
  <VFEC_Thermaebath.label>温泉浴场</VFEC_Thermaebath.label>
  <!-- EN: A very large, heated stone bath meant to be shared by several patrons. Provides a temporary respite from an otherwise discomforting world. When in high numbers, bathers are known to lose themselves in the moment and share more than they normally would. -->
  <VFEC_Thermaebath.description>一个用石头建造的大浴场，可以被多人同时使用。可以让人从残酷的现实中暂时解脱，享受一时的舒适。当泡澡的人数多起来后，他们有可能会控几不住寄几。</VFEC_Thermaebath.description>
  
</LanguageData>